column2: The §Y$JOB$§! is your advisor on matters of diplomacy. The position is traditionally considered the highest on the council.
The §Y$JOB$§! is the councillor in charge of the military. When the ruler cannot or will not command armies, the §Y$JOB$§! will do it.
The §Y$JOB$§! is your personal advisor on matters of the faith, but does not necessarily have to belong to the clergy.
§Y$JOB$§! is an unofficial position on the council. The office holder is responsible for all matters of intrigue and skullduggery.
The §Y$JOB$§! helps you collect taxes and administer your demesne.
